de.uni_jena.bio.informatik.input

Class InputData

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_jena.bio.informatik.input.InputData

  • public class InputData
extends java.lang.Object
    InputData.

    Usage

    1. Accepts user input in the form of directory path userInput. Sorts the files in the directory
    2. Creates an InputData object InputData and calls the userInput userInput to ask for user input
    3. Extracts mz and intensity values as array extractMzIntensity and checks for empty spectra
    4. Extracts mz and intensity values as array extractMzIntensity
    5. Generates match list using 2 spectra as input
    6. Calculates distance between two mz lists specDistance
    7. Transposes the distance matrix transposeFloat
    8. Generates a sparse matrix of this distance matrix generateSparseMatrix
    9. Sparse matrix is traversed to perform recalibration starting from the two mz lists having the minimum distance traverseSortedSet
    Author:
    Purva Kulkarni
